1 Introduction

This document presents the results obtained following the harmonization of 13 annual CCHS cycles using the cchsflow package. The unweighted summary statistics were obtained by cycle, sex, age group and sex-age group, and the code used to obtain them is described below.

It should be noted that the long label was used instead of the short one. Data for the 2021 and 2023 cycles in the territories is not currently available.

2 Define the functions to be used in this document

# Create a not in operator:
`%notin%` <- purrr::negate(`%in%`)

# factor levels and labels
decode_labels <- function(x) {
  if (is.factor(x) && !is.null(attr(x, "labels"))) {
    labels_attr <- attr(x, "labels")
    label_names <- names(labels_attr)
    label_values <- as.character(labels_attr)

    # Replace factor levels with label names
    new_levels <- levels(x)
    replaced_levels <- sapply(new_levels, function(lvl) {
      idx <- which(label_values == lvl)
      if (length(idx) > 0) label_names[idx] else lvl
    })
    levels(x) <- replaced_levels
  }
  return(x)
}

decode_labels2 <- function(x) {
  if (!is.null(attr(x, "label_long"))) {
    labels_attr <- attr(x, "label_long")
  } else if (!is.null(attr(x, "label"))) {
    labels_attr <- attr(x, "label")
  } else {
    labels_attr <- names(df)[which(sapply(names(df), function(name) identical(df[[name]], x)))]
  }
  return(labels_attr)
}

# simple summary stats
split_summary <- function(data) {
  results <- list()

  for (varname in names(data)) {
    variable <- data[[varname]]
    var_label <- attr(variable, "label_long", exact = TRUE)
    if (is.null(var_label)) var_label <- varname
    var_class <- class(variable)[1]

    variable <- decode_labels(variable)

    row <- list(
      Variable = varname,
      Label = var_label,
      Class = var_class
    )

    if (is.numeric(variable)) {
      row$Min <- min(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Q1 <- quantile(variable, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Median <- median(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Mean <- mean(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Q3 <- quantile(variable, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Max <- max(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$N <- sum(!is.na(variable))
      row$NAs <- sum(is.na(variable))
    } else if (is.factor(variable) || is.character(variable)) {
      freq_table <- table(variable, useNA = "no")
      for (i in seq_along(freq_table)) {
        row[[paste0("Level_", i)]] <- names(freq_table)[i]
        row[[paste0("Count_", i)]] <- as.integer(freq_table[i])
      }
      row$NAs <- sum(is.na(variable))
    } else if (is.logical(variable)) {
      row$Count_TRUE <- sum(variable == TRUE, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$Count_FALSE <- sum(variable == FALSE, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$NAs <- sum(is.na(variable))
    } else if (inherits(variable, "Date")) {
      row$MinDate <- min(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$MaxDate <- max(variable, na.rm = TRUE)
      row$NAs <- sum(is.na(variable))
    } else {
      row$Note <- "Unsupported type"
    }

    results[[length(results) + 1]] <- as_tibble(row)
  }

  bind_rows(results)
}


# Define summary function by groups
summarize_variables_by_group <- function(df, vars, group_vars) {
  vars <- vars[vars %notin% group_vars]

  results <- list()

  for (varname in vars) {
    variable <- df[[varname]]
    var_label2 <- decode_labels2(df[[varname]])

    # Convert group_vars to labels (assuming they're factors)
    df <- df %>%
      mutate(across(all_of(group_vars), ~ as_label(.x)))

    if (is.logical(variable)) {
      summary <- df %>%
        group_by(across(all_of(group_vars))) %>%
        summarise(
          Variable = varname,
          Class = "logical",
          `Long label` = var_label2,
          Group_Label = first(.data[[group_vars[1]]]), # Capture label
          Count_TRUE = sum(.data[[varname]] == TRUE, na.rm = TRUE),
          Count_FALSE = sum(.data[[varname]] == FALSE, na.rm = TRUE),
          NAs = sum(is.na(.data[[varname]])),
          .groups = "drop"
        )
    } else if (is.numeric(variable)) {
      summary <- df %>%
        group_by(across(all_of(group_vars))) %>%
        summarise(
          Variable = varname,
          Class = "numeric",
          `Long label` = var_label2,
          Group_Label = first(.data[[group_vars[1]]]), # Capture label
          Mean = mean(.data[[varname]], na.rm = TRUE),
          SD = sd(.data[[varname]], na.rm = TRUE),
          Min = min(.data[[varname]], na.rm = TRUE),
          Median = median(.data[[varname]], na.rm = TRUE),
          Max = max(.data[[varname]], na.rm = TRUE),
          N = sum(!is.na(.data[[varname]])),
          NAs = sum(is.na(.data[[varname]])),
          .groups = "drop"
        )
    } else if (is.factor(variable) || is.character(variable) || inherits(variable, "labelled")) {
      var_label <- get_label(variable, def.value = varname)

      summary <- df %>%
        mutate(Level = as_label(.data[[varname]])) %>%
        group_by(across(all_of(group_vars)), Level) %>%
        summarise(
          Variable = varname,
          Class = "factor/character",
          `Long label` = var_label2,
          Group_Label = first(.data[[group_vars[1]]]), # Capture label
          Count = n(),
          .groups = "drop"
        ) %>%
        relocate(Variable, `Long label`, Group_Label, .before = everything())
    } else {
      summary <- tibble(
        Variable = varname,
        Note = "Unsupported type"
      )
    }

    results[[length(results) + 1]] <- summary
  }

  bind_rows(results) %>%
    select(-Group_Label)
}

# Create the age group as a factor with 18 levels
df <- merged_transfCCHS %>%
  mutate(AGEG = case_when(
    DHH_AGE >= 12 & DHH_AGE < 15 ~ 1,

    DHH_AGE >= 20 & DHH_AGE < 25 ~ 3,
    DHH_AGE >= 25 & DHH_AGE < 30 ~ 4,

    DHH_AGE >= 40 & DHH_AGE < 45 ~ 7,

4 Summary statistics

# Generate summary statistics
summary_tbl <- split_summary(df)

# Select the variables of interest to generate the summary statistics by groups
df <- df %>%
  select(DHH_AGE, DHH_SEX, GEOGPRV, SMKDSTY_A, smoke_simple, SMKG01C_cont, SMKG040_cont, time_quit_smoking, pack_years_cat, Cycle, AGEG)

# Variables of interest
vars <- names(df)

# Generate the summary stats by cycle (but removing empty cycles). The level NA(c) is only assigned in cchsflow when the variable is not a continuous variable
summary_tbl_cycle <- summarize_variables_by_group(df, vars, group_vars = c("Cycle")) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Mean) | (!is.na(Level) & Level != "NA(c)")) %>%
  arrange(Class)

# Generate the summary stats by sex
summary_tbl_sex <- summarize_variables_by_group(df, vars, group_vars = c("DHH_SEX")) %>%
  arrange(Class)

# Generate the summary stats by province\territory
summary_tbl_prov <- summarize_variables_by_group(df, vars, group_vars = c("GEOGPRV")) %>%
  arrange(Class)

# Generate the summary stats by age group
summary_tbl_age_grp <- summarize_variables_by_group(df, vars, group_vars = c("AGEG")) %>%
  arrange(Class)

# Generate the summary stats by age group and sex
summary_tbl_sex_ageg <- summarize_variables_by_group(df, vars, group_vars = c("DHH_SEX", "AGEG")) %>%
  arrange(Class)

# Check population counts in the territories by cycle
summary_tbl_cycle2 <- summary_tbl_cycle %>%
  select(Cycle, Variable, NAs, `Long label`, Level, Count) %>%
  filter(Variable == "GEOGPRV" & Level == "YT/NT/NU")
